The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Etah, April 14 (PTI): Varun Gandhi today promised in writing not to make provocative speeches, a day after the Supreme Court insisted on such an undertaking for his release on bail.          
	His lawyer Prashant Singh Atal said the affidavit contained a promise not to deliver any hate speech and to follow the election code of conduct. The bail plea of the 29-year-old BJP leader in a hate speech case will come up before the Supreme Court again on April 16.                  
	 Phulbani (PTI): The BJPs controversial candidate for the Kandhamal Lok Sabha seat, Ashok Sahu, was arrested on Tuesday for an alleged hate speech on April 5. He has been sent to judicial custody for two weeks.                  
	 Srinagar: Seven soldiers died when an avalanche triggered by fresh snow in the Shamsbari range in north Kashmir struck a temporary counter-insurgency post on Tuesday. Eight soldiers trapped under snow were rescued.                   
	 The Left-backed Independent candidate in Ponnani is Hussain Randathani, not as mentioned in the report headlined CPM formula churns a green laboratory in Tuesdays edition. We apologise for the mistake.                                                                                                                            
